# Advanced Manufacturing & Engineering Digital-First Cloud Infrastructure Transformation (ATMD)

## Project Overview

ATMD was a newly established legal and engineering-focused organization requiring a complete cloud-native Microsoft infrastructure deployment from scratch. The organization consisted of **6 core users (attorneys and operational staff)** who primarily worked remotely, with minimal need for physical office infrastructure.

Due to the highly mobile nature of legal work, the decision was made to implement a **fully Azure-based, cloud-first Microsoft ecosystem**, eliminating traditional on-premises infrastructure entirely.

The project delivered a secure, scalable Microsoft 365 and Azure-based environment built around identity security, endpoint governance, and secure collaboration.

---

# Core Environment Scope

## User Base

- Total Users: **6**
- Roles:
  - Attorneys (Remote-first legal practitioners)
  - Administrative / Operations Staff
  - Managing Partner / Executive Role
- Usage Model:
  - 90–100% remote access
  - Multi-device access (laptops + mobile)
  - High sensitivity legal document handling

---

# Project Objectives

## Identity & Security

- Deploy cloud-only Microsoft Entra ID
- Enforce MFA across all 6 users
- Implement Zero Trust access model
- Secure legal identity and document access

## Endpoint Management

- Intune-based device management for all 6 endpoints
- Windows Autopilot for zero-touch provisioning
- Device compliance enforcement

## Collaboration & Productivity

- SharePoint Online for legal case collaboration
- Secure document storage with version control
- Controlled external sharing for clients

## Security Governance

- Conditional Access policies
- RBAC-based administrative control
- Microsoft Defender for Endpoint integration

---

# Phase 1 — Azure Tenant Deployment

## Microsoft 365 Tenant Setup

- New Microsoft 365 tenant created for ATMD
- Domain configuration completed
- Exchange Online enabled
- Licensing assigned for **6 Microsoft 365 users**
- DNS and identity federation configured

---

# Phase 2 — Entra ID Architecture

## Identity Design

- Cloud-only Microsoft Entra ID (no on-prem AD)
- Password Hash Sync not required (cloud-native model)
- MFA enforced for all **6 users**
- Self-Service Password Reset enabled
- Conditional Access baseline applied

---

# Phase 3 — Security Baseline

## Conditional Access Policies

- MFA required for all sign-ins (100% coverage)
- Block legacy authentication
- Restrict access to compliant devices only
- Risk-based sign-in protection enabled

---

# Phase 4 — Intune Device Management

## Endpoint Scope

- Total managed devices: **6 corporate endpoints**
- Each user assigned a dedicated managed device

## Policies Applied

- BitLocker encryption enforced
- Microsoft Defender for Endpoint enabled
- USB storage restrictions applied
- Application control policies enforced
- Compliance monitoring enabled per device

---

# Phase 5 — SharePoint Collaboration

## Structure

Designed specifically for a **6-user legal team environment**:

- Legal Case Library (primary working space)
- Client Matter Folders (restricted access per case)
- Executive Document Library
- IT Administration Repository

## Security Controls

- Restricted external sharing
- Sensitivity labels applied to legal documents
- Version control enforced
- Audit logging enabled for all 6 users

---

# Phase 6 — RBAC Model

## Administrative Roles

With only 6 users, RBAC was intentionally simplified:

- 1 × Global Administrator (Senior IT Engineer role)
- 1 × Security Administrator
- Remaining users: Standard legal and operational roles

Principle of least privilege strictly enforced.

---

# Phase 7 — Security Hardening

## Identity Protection

- MFA enforced for all users
- Sign-in risk detection enabled
- Impossible travel detection active
- Session timeout policies enforced

## Endpoint Protection

- Defender for Endpoint deployed to all 6 devices
- Real-time threat monitoring enabled
- Compliance scoring implemented

---

# Deployment Process Summary

1. Microsoft 365 tenant created for **6-user organization**
2. Entra ID configured (cloud-only model)
3. MFA enforced for all users
4. Intune enrolled all 6 endpoints
5. SharePoint collaboration environment deployed
6. Conditional Access policies applied
7. Security hardening completed

